{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8901-bcde-f12345678901",
    "name": "Integration Gateway API",
    "description": "Partner-facing API for submitting diagnostic jobs, polling status, downloading PDF reports, and receiving signed webhooks.\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Start infrastructure: `docker compose up -d`\n2. Apply migrations: `npx prisma migrate deploy`\n3. Seed a Partner in Prisma Studio with `apiKey` matching the `api_key` environment variable (default: `test-key-123`)\n4. Start the API: `npm run start:dev` (run from Windows PowerShell if using Prisma on Windows)\n5. Import **Integration Gateway — Local** environment and select it\n6. Set `callback_url` to your [webhook.site](https://webhook.site) URL to observe outbound webhooks\n\n## Typical flow\n\n1. **Create Job** — saves `job_id` to the environment\n2. **Get Job Status** — poll every few seconds until `status` is `COMPLETED` or `FAILED`; saves `download_token` when ready\n3. **Download Report** — fetches the PDF (only when job is `COMPLETED`)\n\nProcessing takes ~2–10 seconds. Roughly 10% of jobs fail randomly (`PROCESSING_FAILURE_RATE`).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000"
    },
    {
      "key": "api_key",
      "value": "test-key-123"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Jobs",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Job",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.environment.set('idempotency_key', pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 202 Accepted', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(202);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains jobId', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('jobId');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.environment.set('job_id', json.jobId);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "x-api-key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "idempotency-key",
                "value": "{{idempotency_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "metadata",
                  "value": "{\n  \"patientId\": \"P-12345\",\n  \"studyType\": \"OCT\",\n  \"callbackUrl\": \"{{callback_url}}\"\n}",
                  "contentType": "application/json",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "description": "Valid types: image/jpeg, image/png, image/tiff, application/pdf. Magic bytes are verified.",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "fixtures/sample.pdf"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "jobs"]
            },
            "description": "Submit a new diagnostic job with multipart form data.\n\n**Required headers**\n- `x-api-key` — partner API key\n- `idempotency-key` — unique per submission (auto-generated via `{{$guid}}`)\n\n**Body (multipart/form-data)**\n- `metadata` — JSON string with `patientId`, `studyType`, `callbackUrl`\n- `file` — one or more attachments (repeat the `file` field for multiple files)\n\n**Response (202)**\n```json\n{ \"jobId\": \"uuid\", \"status\": \"PENDING\" }\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Job Status",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains jobId and status', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('jobId');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (json.downloadToken) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('download_token', json.downloadToken);",
                  "    console.log('Job completed — download_token saved');",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.log('Job status:', json.status, '— poll again in a few seconds');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "x-api-key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs/{{job_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "jobs", "{{job_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Poll the current status of a job. Scoped to the authenticated partner.\n\n**Response fields**\n- `status` — `PENDING`, `PROCESSING`, `COMPLETED`, or `FAILED`\n- `error` — present when `FAILED`\n- `downloadToken` / `downloadUrl` — present when `COMPLETED` with a report\n- `attachments` — uploaded file metadata\n- `callbackUrl` — webhook destination\n\nRun repeatedly until status is terminal (`COMPLETED` or `FAILED`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Job (Idempotent Replay)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 202 Accepted', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(202);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Returns same jobId as original submission', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const original = pm.environment.get('job_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.jobId).to.eql(original);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "x-api-key",
                "value": "{{api_key}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "idempotency-key",
                "value": "{{idempotency_key}}",
                "description": "Reuses the key from the last Create Job request",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "metadata",
                  "value": "{\n  \"patientId\": \"P-12345\",\n  \"studyType\": \"OCT\",\n  \"callbackUrl\": \"{{callback_url}}\"\n}",
                  "contentType": "application/json",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "fixtures/sample.pdf"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/jobs",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "jobs"]
            },
            "description": "Replays the previous submission using the same `idempotency-key`. Must return the same `jobId` with no side effects.\n\nRun **Create Job** first so `idempotency_key` and `job_id` are set in the environment."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Job submission and status polling endpoints."
    },
    {
      "name": "Reports",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Download Report",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response is a PDF', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/pdf');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/reports/download?token={{download_token}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "reports", "download"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{download_token}}",
                  "description": "Signed downloadToken from a completed job"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Download the completed PDF report. **No API key required** — authentication is via the signed `token` query parameter only.\n\nThe token expires after one hour. Obtain a fresh `downloadToken` by polling **Get Job Status**.\n\n**Success:** `200` with `Content-Type: application/pdf`"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Secure report download via signed token."
    },
